properties.headline: High Surf Advisory issued February 19 at 3:21AM HST until February 21 at 6:00PM HST by NWS Honolulu HI
properties.description:
...HIGH SURF ADVISORY FOR EAST FACING SHORES...

.Strong trade winds will produce high surf along east facing
shores through Friday evening. Surf will subside over the weekend
as the winds subside.

* WHAT...Large breaking waves of 6 to 9 feet.

* WHERE...East facing shores of Kauai, Oahu, Molokai, Maui, and
the Big Island.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM Friday.

* IMPACTS...Moderate. Expect strong breaking waves, shore break,
and strong currents making swimming dangerous.
properties.instruction: Heed all advice from ocean safety officials and exercise caution.

NWSheadline: HIGH SURF ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM HST FRIDAY FOR EAST FACING SHORES OF KAUAI OAHU MOLOKAI MAUI AND THE BIG ISLAND
